            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Brush a little <strong>cold water </strong>around the edges of the pastry (this helps to seal the pastry!)</p><p>Fold the <strong>pastry</strong> over the filling and seal firmly together then use a fork to crimp along the join and prick air holes all over</p><p>Brush the pastry with a little <strong>milk</strong> and top with <strong>half </strong>the<strong> nigella seeds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then put the tray[s] in the oven for 17-20 min or until golden and cooked through – this is your <strong>free range</strong> <strong>chicken curry pasty</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
